<body><bold>Chitin Chestplate<end>
<tab><RECIPE name=chitinChestplate domain=Hivetera>
As our ancestors prepared to engage the undead in battle, it was clear to them that they needed protection for their chests. With this in mind, the used Chitin Plates to fashion chestplates. It is believed that the first chestplate was made by letting ocelots play with Clay Hunters. Some speculate that cats, for this reason, were the world's first mummies.

